The paper focuses on improving the efficiency of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) through pruning and sparse convolutions, which are commonly used in computer vision (CV) applications. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning (LG), artificial intelligence (AI), and neural networks (NE), which are closely related to CV. Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the method on different computer architectures, which falls under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (DC).
